# CODEOWNERS — who must review before merge to main.
#
# Part of the delivery rails (see workflows/RAILS.md and the methodology spec at
# delivery-standard/docs/the-rails.md §4 "The merge bar").
#
# This file is only enforced when the main-branch ruleset has
# pull_request.require_code_owner_review = true (see
# profile/rulesets/branch-protection.json). On a solo repo the sole code owner is
# also the author, so code-owner review cannot be self-satisfied today — the rule is
# "armed" and becomes real the moment a second collaborator joins. Until then the
# repository-admin bypass actor in the ruleset lets the owner still merge. See
# RAILS.md "Solo-repo accommodation".
#
# Order matters: the LAST matching pattern wins for a given file.
#
# ── PLACEHOLDERS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   <<CODE_OWNER>>   The owning user or team handle (reference: @your-org/your-team).
#                    Replace EVERY @your-org/your-team below.
#   <<GATED_PATHS>>  These directory patterns MUST stay in sync with the
#                    <<GATED_PATHS>> regex in workflows/security.yml and the rubric.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Default owner for everything.
*                                       @your-org/your-team

# --- Gated paths: changes here always pull in the code owner, independent of a
#     spec's risk tier (the-rails.md §3 "path-triggered, not just tier-triggered").
#     The security-review workflow also fires on these same paths.

# The rails themselves — the factory. A defect here ships in every change that rides
# the rails afterward, so it is held to the tightest review.
/.github/                               @your-org/your-team
/.claude/settings.json                  @your-org/your-team
/.claude/hooks/                         @your-org/your-team
/scripts/rails/                         @your-org/your-team

# Authentication, identity, and authorization surfaces.
**/Auth/                                @your-org/your-team
**/Identity/                            @your-org/your-team
**/Security/                            @your-org/your-team

# Data migrations.
**/Migrations/                          @your-org/your-team

# Infrastructure as code.
/infra/                                 @your-org/your-team
